data.description: Discover the allure of mountain living without sacrificing the convenience and amenities of Woodland Park, an established, quick growing, and highly desired mountain town! Located in close proximity to the National Forest, there’s an abundance of opportunities for adventure and exploration while being located close to conveniences such as schools, the Park District/Aquatic Center, and downtown dining and shopping. This beautiful 2-bedroom 1-bathroom end unit townhome is nestled in a quiet neighborhood that offers the perfect blend of comfort and convenience. At 847-square-feet, this mountain retreat cleverly maximizes space with a thoughtful layout that doesn't compromise on comfort. The main level's openness, vaulted ceilings, and plentiful windows complemented by the free standing wood burning stove, gives the illusion of a much larger space. In addition to the fresh coat of paint, the main level of the home has brand new LVP flooring (12/1/23) which is easy to clean and maintain and provides a seamless transition between living spaces. The new high-end GE Profile wi-fi washer and dryer will also be staying with the house! The real charm of this home, however, lies beyond its walls. Step outside onto the expansive wrap-around deck and soak in the breathtaking views of Pikes Peak. The outdoor area seamlessly extends your living space, providing an ideal spot to savor your morning coffee or host get togethers with friends. The fully fenced in backyard provides plenty of flat usable space, a built in fire pit, as well as a handful of mature trees scattered throughout the backyard which is surrounded by 29 newly planted Skyrocket Juniper trees (quick growing and projected to reach 15-18ft), ensuring plenty of shade and privacy as they continue to grow. With the freedom of no HOA fees or restrictions, this townhome an excellent choice for both a primary residence and a savvy investment opportunity for rental income.
